The paper introduces a new framework for expressing and reasoning with probabilistic and deterministic information, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the development of a new search algorithm, which is relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper defines the semantics and graphical representation of the mixed networks, which is relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
